											    	<em>The following is from Laila Lalami's </em>The Dream Hotel<em>. Lalami is the author of five books. Her books have been translated into twenty languages. Lalamiâ€™s writing appears regularly in the </em>Los Angeles Times, The Washington Post, The Nation, Harperâ€™s, The Guardian,<em> and </em>The New York Times<em>. She has been awarded fellowships from the British Council, the Fulbright Program, the Guggenheim Foundation, and the Radcliffe Institute at Harvard University. She lives in Los Angeles.</em>											    </div>
